Suggests: vosk-model-small-en-us
Description: Offline voice-to-text daemon for Linux
 A privacy-first, fully offline voice dictation daemon that integrates
 natively with the Linux desktop environment. It monitors system-wide
 input focus, automatically activates microphone listening when a text
 field is active, and injects transcribed text directly into the active
 window using a kernel-level virtual keyboard (uinput).
 .
 Features:
  - 100% offline speech recognition via Vosk
  - Context-aware focus detection (X11 and Wayland)
  - Virtual keyboard text injection via uinput
  - GNOME desktop integration (optional HUD overlay)
  - Sub-500ms transcription latency
